widgets_values:
Audio Filter Cutoffs

Available Frequency spectrum = 0hz to 22050hz

Low Cutoff (hz): Frequencies below the set value will be filtered out (i.e. not used to drive reactivity). Keep this > 100-200hz in most cases, you don't really want the super low end since that will tend to cause phase issues and hurt the reactivity.

High Cutoff (hz): Frequencies below the set value will be filtered out (i.e. not used to drive reactivity).

Implicit middle band: The low and high cutoff are used to calculate the middle frequency band.

nodes.title: Color Correct
widgets_values: Adjust contrast of the grayscaled-colormask before input to QR code controlnet. Help prevent dark spots while helping keep the form of the mask in the final output.

Audio2Weights Nodes

These nodes 
1. Process the audio signal
2. Separate the audio into 3 frequency bands (low, mid, high)
3. Convert the bands into frame values which can be used for scheduling

Schedule Audio Framesync

amp_control = dynamic range of the signal, i.e. the range of movement of the mask. 1 = full range of movement, 0 = no movement.

amp_offset = the minimum value of the signal, i.e. the smallest size of the mask. 1 = always full max size (not recommended), 0 = when audio is silent shape size is 0.  

These settings will vary depending on the song and how you want the shapes to overlap.

nodes.title: Scheduled Binary Comparison
widgets_values:
The nodes take a grayscale image and turns it into a binary (black and white) image according to a given threshold.

Comparison Schedule: Takes a threshold value for each frame from 0-1. Given a perfect gradient, value 0 would return all white and value 1 would return all black. So, value 0.5 would turn all pixels > 0.5 black and < 0.5 white.

Use Epsilon: Essentially turns the shape hollow. So if you have, for example, circular gradient input image, it'll return a donut shaped mask.

Epsilon Schedule: when use_epsilon is enabled, the epsilon schedule controls the thickness of the shape.

nodes.title: Switches and composit
widgets_values:
橙色的节点皆可调整，不同的设定都有不同的结果，多尝试，选择你最喜欢的
There are two switches and a compositing node below:
1.Invert Generator 1: Inverts the image from generator 1 to create different geometric shapes. 
2.Invert Generator 2: Inverts The second Generator to create different geometric shapes. 
3.Pointer Duff Image Composite: Changes the way the images interact with each-other and gives you more control over how the images interact with each-other.

nodes.title: Color Mask Compositing
widgets_values:
This compositing set up stacks the color masks like so:

center: yellow
middle: green
outer: red
background: magenta

FYI, in addition to being used for the IPA and conditioning, this mask gets turned to grayscale and fed into the QR code controlnet the contrast between these colors actually has an effect on the output. So you may want to adjust to taste depending on what you're going for.
